## ğŸš€ How to Install

### For Android Users:
1. Download the APK from the [Releases](https://github.com/ABBAS-PROJECT/StudyBuddy/releases) page
2. Transfer the APK to your Android device
3. Enable "Install from unknown sources" in your device settings
4. Open the APK and install
5. Enjoy tracking your study sessions!

**Requirements:** Android 5.0 or higher

## ğŸ’» For Developers

### Prerequisites
- Visual Studio 2022 (v17.14+)
- .NET 9 SDK
- .NET MAUI workload installed

### Setup
1. Clone this repository
```bash
git clone https://github.com/ABBAS-PROJECT/StudyBuddy.git
```

2. Open `StudyBuddy.sln` in Visual Studio

3. The app is already configured with Firebase - it works out of the box!

4. Select your target platform (Android/iOS/Windows)

5. Build and run (F5)

### Firebase Configuration (Optional)
If you want to use your own Firebase database:
1. Create a Firebase project at https://console.firebase.google.com
2. Enable Realtime Database
3. Update the Firebase URL in `FirebaseHelper.cs` (line 11)
4. Set database rules to allow read/write access

